Drop libsysbase sys_lwmutex_* wrapper bodies.

The wrappers in libgloss/libsysbase/lock.c routed sys_lwmutex_* through
the __syscalls indirection table.  That worked when no real SPRX
trampoline existed for those NIDs, but the nidgen-emitted liblv2_stub.a
now provides them as canonical SPRX trampolines (with PSL1GHT-style
sysLwMutex* aliases).  Keeping both copies caused duplicate
sysPrxForUser .lib.stub records and the stale-build / TOC-slot
collision documented in docs/abi/cellos-lv2-abi-spec.md §5.1.

Resolution: keep lock.c as a comment-only placeholder so the
libsysbase Makefile.in OBJS list (which already names lock.o) still
finds a translation unit, but produce no symbols.  The trampolines in
liblv2_stub.a are the only definition of sys_lwmutex_*.

